# MCP FileSystem Server Ultimate - OAuth Configuration Examples
# Copy this file to .env and configure your OAuth provider

# ============================================================================
# OAUTH CONFIGURATION (Choose ONE provider)
# ============================================================================

# ----- AUTH0 CONFIGURATION -----
# Uncomment and configure for Auth0:
# OAUTH_PROVIDER=auth0
# OAUTH_JWKS_URL=https://your-domain.auth0.com/.well-known/jwks.json
# OAUTH_ISSUER=https://your-domain.auth0.com/
# OAUTH_AUDIENCE=https://api.lukhas.dev
# OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your-auth0-client-id
# OAUTH_REQUIRED_SCOPES=read:files,write:files,execute:commands

# ----- KEYCLOAK CONFIGURATION -----
# Uncomment and configure for Keycloak:
# OAUTH_PROVIDER=keycloak
# OAUTH_JWKS_URL=https://keycloak.yourdomain.com/realms/lukhas/protocol/openid-connect/certs
# OAUTH_ISSUER=https://keycloak.yourdomain.com/realms/lukhas
# OAUTH_AUDIENCE=mcp-fs-lukhas
# OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=mcp-fs-lukhas
# OAUTH_REQUIRED_SCOPES=files:read,files:write,commands:execute

# ----- CLOUDFLARE ACCESS CONFIGURATION -----
# Uncomment and configure for Cloudflare Access:
# OAUTH_PROVIDER=cloudflare
# OAUTH_JWKS_URL=https://your-account.cloudflareaccess.com/cdn-cgi/access/certs
# OAUTH_ISSUER=https://your-account.cloudflareaccess.com
# OAUTH_AUDIENCE=your-cloudflare-application-aud
# OAUTH_REQUIRED_SCOPES=read,write,execute

# ============================================================================
# MCP SERVER CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================

# File system root (REQUIRED)
MCP_FS_ROOT=/Users/agi_dev/LOCAL-REPOS/Lukhas

# Maximum file size in bytes (default: 2MB)
MCP_MAX_BYTES=2097152

# OAuth JWT cache TTL in milliseconds (default: 5 minutes)
OAUTH_CACHE_TTL=300000

# ============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT vs PRODUCTION MODES
# ============================================================================

# DEVELOPMENT MODE (No OAuth):
# - Comment out all OAUTH_* variables above
# - Server runs without authentication
# - Use for local development and testing

# PRODUCTION MODE (OAuth Required):
# - Configure one OAuth provider above
# - All requests must include valid JWT Bearer token
# - Use for ChatGPT integration and production deployment

# ============================================================================
# QUICK START EXAMPLES
# ============================================================================

# 1. For Auth0 (fastest setup):
#    - Create Auth0 account and API
#    - Set OAUTH_PROVIDER=auth0 and configure URLs above
#    - Get access token: curl -X POST https://your-domain.auth0.com/oauth/token

# 2. For local development (no auth):
#    - Comment out all OAUTH_* variables
#    - Run: npm run start

# 3. For production deployment:
#    - Configure OAuth provider above
#    - Run: npm run start:oauth
#    - ChatGPT connects with Bearer token authentication
